main event: A round object with yellow streaks and a green center was sighted in Lake Leelanau, Michigan in 1956.
interesting points: The object changed from a round shape to a funnel shape,The sighting lasted for one hour and five minutes,The observers used binoculars to view the object,The sighting was concluded to be caused by the planet Venus,The object was reported to have bright colors and irregular movements.
sighted object: round object with yellow streaks and green center
